The numerous specimens collected by RAMoN DE LA SAGRA agree well with each other and with WRIGHT n. 2792 in the Kew Herbarium. The specimen from Loma Pelada, which is the V. stiotophylla WRIGHT, appears to be only a shade form of the species, being collected in »damp‚ shady woods». It has greenish involucres, those of genuine V. havanensis often being purple-tinged.
